  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Extremely disappointing care&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;After receiving an injury which required an x-ray, I made my way (with difficulty) to the main entrance as that’s where I had been dropped off. The kind reception lady saw the pain I was in and arranged for someone to wheel me back to A&amp;amp;amp;E. After checking in (which was straight-forward and polite), I was wheeled to the seating area and told to take a seat and that the wheelchair would be taken away. I hadn’t even sat down when I was called through to triage. While I was pleased to be called so quickly, the person with the wheelchair made a rapid exit and did not offer to help me to the room. I virtually had to hop to the triage room whereby someone asked what had happened, did not examine the injury but said I needed an x-ray and sent me to the urgent care unit. Again, I had to hop/limp/hobble down there. I then waited for 2 hours before being called for an x-ray and then a further hour and a half after the x-ray for the results. The final indignity was being called by the doctor to discuss the results. He saw me struggling to make my way to him and then decided to leave me stood in the hallway for a few minutes while he went into the office to discuss something else with the staff in there. I was literally clinging onto the wall for support. I am thoroughly disappointed with the quality of care I received. The most care I got was from the receptionists, not the medical staff. I have even had to order and pay for my own crutches as none were offered despite my difficulty in walking (neither were painkillers or a compress).&lt;/CommentText&gt;
